  "prompt": "What Pok\u00e9mon hatches from Eggs in Pok\u00e9mon GO?",
  "response": "In Pok\u00e9mon GO, many different Pok\u00e9mon can hatch from Eggs, which are obtained from Pok\u00e9Stops. The specific Pok\u00e9mon that can hatch varies depending on the Egg type (2km, 5km, 7km, 10km, and 12km Eggs) and can change periodically with updates to the game. Some examples include:\n\n2km Eggs: Pichu, Cleffa, Igglybuff, Togepi, Pidgey, Rattata\n5km Eggs: Eevee, Electabuzz, Magmar, Drowzee, Machop\n7km Eggs: Regional Alolan and Galarian forms\n10km Eggs: Lapras, Dratini, Beldum, Gible\n12km Eggs: Weird/Dark-type Pok\u00e9mon like Pawniard, Vullaby, Deino\n\nThe specific Pok\u00e9mon in Eggs can change with game updates, so the current pool may differ from this list.",
